SUBSTITUTE FOR
SENATE BILL NO. 728
A bill to amend 1998 PA 58, entitled
"Michigan liquor control code of 1998,"
by amending section 507 (MCL 436.1507).
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 507. (1) The commission may issue, without regard to the
2 quota provisions requirement of section 531, licenses to the owner
3 or lessee, or both, to sell alcoholic beverages for consumption on
4 the premises of buildings in the passenger terminal complex of each
5 publicly owned airport that is served by scheduled commercial
6 passenger airlines certificated to enplane and deplane passengers
7 on a scheduled basis by the federal aviation agency or the civil
8 aeronautics board.Federal Aviation Administration.
9 (2) Notwithstanding anything in this act to the contrary, a
DAW S05062'25 (S-1) yfmpw4

2
1 customer who purchases alcoholic liquor from a licensee described
2 in subsection (1) or a licensee that holds both a license described
3 in subsection (1) and a specially designated merchant license
4 issued under section 533(5)(a) may possess and consume that
5 alcoholic liquor at any unlicensed place in the passenger terminal
6 complex subject to the approval of the governing body of the
7 publicly owned airport.
8 (3) A customer that purchases alcoholic liquor at a location
9 described in subsection (2) from a licensee shall not consume the
10 alcoholic liquor on the licensed premises of another licensee. A
11 licensee shall not allow the consumption of alcoholic liquor under
12 subsection (2) on its licensed premises if the alcoholic liquor was
13 not purchased from the licensee.
14 (4) A licensee shall not sell or serve alcoholic liquor under
15 subsection (2) to a customer outside of the licensed premises of
16 the licensee.
17 (5) A license issued under this section is not transferable.
